      "span_text": "Finally, we take into account the symmetry breaking restrictions concerning the functions f and g in Equations (A19) and (A20), as described in Section 3.3 in  , and obtain the infinitesimals of the viscous Hopf-Burgers FDE: where a 4 , a 5 , a 6 , a 7 ∈ R are arbitrary constants, a 1 (t) and a 2 (t) = A 2 (t) are arbitrary functions and g is an arbitrary functional, which has to fulfill the viscous Hopf-Burgers FDE."
